<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1657,2044]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1765,1791]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[827,973,1765,1791]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Abu-Zoherah, R. &amp; Al-Taher, K. &amp; Tilkian, S." box="[1014,1314,1765,1792]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref33021" refString="Abu-Zoherah, R., Al-Taher, K. &amp; Tilkian, S. (1993) List of Insects Recorded from Saudi Arabia. Ministry of Agriculture and Water, National Agriculture and Water Research Center, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, Riyadh, Academic Publishing &amp; Press, Ministry of Agriculture and Water, Riyadh, 394 pp." type="book" year="1993">
Abu-Zoherah 
<emphasis box="[1172,1222,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. (1993)
</bibRefCitation>
. It was described from the “Ostindien” (East Indies), without further information as to which parts of East Indies. Since it also occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[263,481,1837,1864]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[538,623,1837,1863]" name="Taiwan" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, it probably occurs throughout the East Indies (
<bibRefCitation author="Thompson, F. C. &amp; Vockeroth, J. R." pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="437 - 458" refId="ref41008" refString="Thompson, F. C. &amp; Vockeroth, J. R. (1989) Family Syrphidae. In: Evenhuis, N. L. (Ed.), Catalog of the Diptera of the Australasian and Oceanian Regions. Bishop Museum Press, Honolulu and E. J. Brill, Leiden, pp. 437 - 458." type="book chapter" year="1989">Thompson &amp; Vockeroth 1989</bibRefCitation>
). It is widespread in the Oriental (
<collectingCountry box="[596,658,1873,1899]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[669,764,1873,1899]" name="Pakistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[820,932,1873,1900]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
) and Afrotropical Region including Réunion (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, K. G. V. &amp; Vockeroth, J. R." box="[159,435,1909,1935]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="488 - 510" refId="ref40306" refString="Smith, K. G. V. &amp; Vockeroth, J. R. (1980) 38. Family Syrphidae. In: Crosskey R. W. (Ed.), Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afro- tropical Region. British Museum (Natural History), London, pp. 488 - 510." type="book chapter" year="1980">Smith &amp;Vockeroth 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Peck, L. V." box="[446,566,1909,1935]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref38699" refString="Peck, L. V. (1988) Family Syrphidae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Syrphidae- Conopidae. Vol. 8. Akademiai Kiado, Budapest, pp. 11 - 230." type="book" year="1988">Peck 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Whittington, A. E." box="[576,777,1909,1935]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="579 - 607" refId="ref41868" refString="Whittington, A. E. (2003) The Afrotropical Syrphidae fauna: an assessment. Studia dipterologica, 10 (2), 579 - 607." type="journal article" year="2003">Whittington 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ghorpade, K." box="[788,964,1909,1935]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref35870" refString="Ghorpade, K. (2014) An updated Check-list of the Hover-flies (Diptera: Syrphidae) recorded in the Indian subcontinent. Colemania, 44, 1 - 30." type="journal article" year="2014">Ghorpadé 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sengupta, J. &amp; Naskar, A. &amp; Maity, A. &amp; Hazra, S. &amp; Mukhopadhyay, E. &amp; Banerjee, D. &amp; Ghosh, S." box="[974,1207,1909,1936]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="381 - 396" refId="ref39972" refString="Sengupta, J., Naskar, A., Maity, A., Hazra, S., Mukhopadhyay, E., Banerjee, D. &amp; Ghosh, S. (2016) An updated distributional account of Indian Hover flies (insect: Diptera: Syrphidae). Journal of Entomology and Zoology, 4 (6), 381 - 396." type="journal article" year="2016">
Sengupta 
<emphasis box="[1085,1133,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Within the Arabian Peninsula, previously known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[605,683,1946,1972]" name="Yemen" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smit, J. T. &amp; van Harten, A. &amp; Ketelaar, R." box="[699,888,1945,1972]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref40237" refString="Smit, J. T., van Harten, A. &amp; Ketelaar, R. (2017) Order Diptera, family Syrphidae the hoverflies of the Arabian Peninsula. In: van Harten, A. (Eds.), Arthropod fauna of the UAE. Vol. 6. Department of the President's Affairs, Abu Dhabi, pp. 572 - 612." type="book" year="2017">
Smit 
<emphasis box="[762,812,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). There is a series of adults from 
<collectingCountry box="[1269,1353,1945,1971]" name="Nigeria" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
(Zaria, Samaru) in NMWC reared in 1979 from larvae that were almost destroying a psyllid colony (gen. nov. nr. 
<emphasis box="[1321,1427,1982,2008]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Arytainia</emphasis>
) on 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schumach.) Milne-Redh" authorityName="Milne-Redh" baseAuthorityName="Schumach." box="[186,729,2017,2044]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Piliostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thonningii">
<emphasis box="[186,437,2017,2043]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Piliostigma thonningii</emphasis>
(Schumach.) Milne-Redh
</taxonomicName>
leaves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,150,284]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,150,176]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</emphasis>
Larvae of this species have been recorded as predators of the African psyllid 
<taxonomicName authority="(Del Guercio)" baseAuthorityName="Del Guercio" baseAuthorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Triozidae" genus="Trioza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erytreae">
<emphasis box="[1206,1378,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Trioza erytreae</emphasis>
(Del Guercio)
</taxonomicName>
, a serious citrus pest (
<bibRefCitation author="Quilici, S. &amp; Leciant, F. &amp; Delvare, G. &amp; Vercambre, B." box="[496,703,186,213]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref39120" refString="Quilici, S., Leciant, F., Delvare, G. &amp; Vercambre, B. (1988) Aphids and their natural enemies of Reunion island: a review and new observations. In: Niemczyk, E. &amp; Dixon, A. F. G. (Eds.), Ecology and Effectiveness of Aphidophaga. SPB Academic Publishing, The Hague, pp. 111 - 117." type="book chapter" year="1988">
Quilici 
<emphasis box="[582,630,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 1988
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Al-Ahmadi, A. Z. &amp; Salem, M. M." box="[721,1076,186,212]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref33124" refString="Al-Ahmadi, A. Z. &amp; Salem, M. M. (2000) Entomofauna of Saudi Arabia, Part II: Checklist of Phytophagous Insect. Academic Publishing &amp; Press, King Saud University, Riyadh, 187 pp." type="book" year="2000">Al-Ahmadi &amp; Salem (2000: 29)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Del Guercio" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[1186,1305,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Triozidae" genus="Trioza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erytreae">
<emphasis box="[1186,1305,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">T. erytreae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
as a pest of citrus trees but there is no record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1830" box="[777,930,222,249]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Baccha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sapphirina">
<emphasis box="[777,930,222,249]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">A. sapphirina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
attacking this pest in 
<collectingRegion box="[1178,1240,223,249]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="Jizan" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Jazan</collectingRegion>
and this needs to be investigated.
</paragraph>
